WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.878
♪

00:02.878 --> 00:04.338
Oliver Putnam, long considered

00:04.338 --> 00:07.424
New York's most un-land-able bachelor,
is in love.

00:07.424 --> 00:10.552
That's right. This merchandise
is off the market, bruh.

00:10.552 --> 00:13.096
Ah! Loretta.
Whom you have yet to ask out.

00:17.100 --> 00:18.101
[text whooshes]

00:19.311 --> 00:20.854
<i>You're not supposed to be here.</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:22.898
There was someone in his dressing room.

00:22.898 --> 00:24.608
Whose lipstick is this?

00:24.608 --> 00:26.235
I would imagine
it belongs to our killer.

00:26.235 --> 00:28.612
You found my lipstick.

00:28.612 --> 00:31.823
Charles-Haden Savage, I'd be honored.

00:31.823 --> 00:33.617
The answer is yes.

00:33.617 --> 00:36.161
I would love to marry you!

00:36.161 --> 00:37.913
This is a fun twist.

00:43.001 --> 00:46.004
♪ gentle melody playing ♪

00:46.004 --> 00:48.799
[birds chirping]
[breeze blowing]

00:48.799 --> 00:51.593
[bicycles rattling]

00:52.010 --> 00:55.138
JOY:
<i>Ah, love! You gotta love it.</i>

00:55.138 --> 00:58.934
<i>Everywhere you look, there it is.</i>

00:58.934 --> 01:01.311
<i>But in the city that never sleeps,</i>

01:01.311 --> 01:03.939
<i>how do you really know
who the hell you're sleeping with?</i>

01:04.648 --> 01:07.901
<i>People can conceal
some very dirty secrets.</i>

01:07.901 --> 01:09.194
[knocking]

01:09.194 --> 01:12.072
[glass shattering]
[grunting, yelling]

01:12.072 --> 01:14.700
<i>Or fatally fatal flaws.</i>

01:14.700 --> 01:16.076
[Oliver growls]

01:16.076 --> 01:17.911
[nervous laughter]
[Joy muttering]

01:17.911 --> 01:19.955
Everything's fine.
[glass shattering]

01:19.955 --> 01:20.956
[shuts door]

01:20.956 --> 01:23.500
Joy's just loudly shattering sea glass
to put in her aquarium.

01:23.500 --> 01:24.877
Sure, sure.

01:24.877 --> 01:27.296
Uh, have you asked your new fiancée
about the lipstick yet?

01:27.296 --> 01:30.257
Did she write "fucking pig"
on Ben's dressing room mirror?

01:30.257 --> 01:32.718
[laughs] Oh yeah. No. But, I will.

01:32.718 --> 01:34.928
Charles, you said
you would ask her two days ago.

01:34.928 --> 01:36.430
Let us in. We can talk to her.

01:36.430 --> 01:39.558
I am handling the situation
in my own time.

01:39.558 --> 01:41.518
- [glass shatters]
- See, I told you he didn't need our help,

01:41.518 --> 01:43.687
but I do. Does this scarf say,

01:43.687 --> 01:46.148
"Loretta, I've loved you
since the first day I met you"?

01:46.148 --> 01:49.651
I don't know what the scarf is saying,
but all I can see is a crayon box.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.195
OLIVER:
Ah. Well, see, that's why

01:51.195 --> 01:53.197
we always carry a backup.

01:53.864 --> 01:55.866
- Thank you, Mabel.
- Charles,

01:55.866 --> 01:57.576
I can calmly talk to Joy.

01:57.576 --> 02:00.245
You know,
investigator woman to suspect woman.

02:00.245 --> 02:03.332
She is not another Jan. I... think.
She <i>could</i> be

02:03.332 --> 02:05.876
but it's important for me
to be able to interrogate

02:05.876 --> 02:08.754
my murderous girlfriend... fiancée...

02:08.754 --> 02:10.047
[Joy yells, glass shatters]
Shit.

02:10.047 --> 02:11.882
What about my hair?

02:11.882 --> 02:13.050
Is it giving Karen...

02:13.050 --> 02:15.135
[imitating Cary Grant]
<i>or Cary Grant?</i>

02:15.135 --> 02:17.471
Hold on. [stammering]

02:17.471 --> 02:20.349
- Mabel Mora, are you going out on a date?
- Date?

02:20.349 --> 02:22.851
No! I-- No. No.

02:22.851 --> 02:24.728
Tobert has a suspect he has a lead on.

02:24.728 --> 02:26.480
I'm meeting him for a stakeout,

02:26.480 --> 02:28.482
and the place has a dress code.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.484
- Well, it's a date.
- Yeah.

02:30.484 --> 02:33.362
It's a stakeout!
When two totally platonic,

02:33.362 --> 02:36.031
semi-professional investigators
wait together,

02:36.031 --> 02:38.158
in an out-of-sight, enclosed space,

02:38.158 --> 02:41.036
and watch while a suspect
hopefully incriminates themselves,

02:41.036 --> 02:43.121
while we hold in our pee for hours
[Joy grunts, glass shatters]

02:43.121 --> 02:44.540
and eat stale Cheetos.

02:44.540 --> 02:46.542
In a cocktail dress.

02:46.542 --> 02:48.544
Look, I'm gonna unmute your texts.

02:48.544 --> 02:50.587
I'll be in the wings
if anything should go haywire.

02:50.587 --> 02:51.588
[Joy screams, glass shatters]

02:51.588 --> 02:53.131
[Charles laughs nervously]
[twists door knob]

02:53.131 --> 02:55.717
I'll be okay.
[Joy grunts, glass shatters]

02:56.218 --> 02:58.929
[Joy screams, glass shatters]
[door shuts]

02:58.929 --> 03:00.430
[growls] Oy.

03:01.223 --> 03:05.143
JOY: <i>Is it possible you're sleeping
next to a lunatic, or a liar?</i>

03:05.143 --> 03:06.687
<i>Sure, it is.</i>
[elevator dings]

03:06.687 --> 03:07.855
♪

03:07.855 --> 03:10.566
<i>But I always tell people,
better lose your mind loving</i>

03:10.566 --> 03:12.609
<i>than to live your life loveless.</i>

03:12.609 --> 03:14.903
It's been a while
since I dipped my quill

03:14.903 --> 03:16.738
in a woman's ink pot.

03:16.738 --> 03:19.283
Any new moves I should know about?

03:19.283 --> 03:21.410
Please don't make me take the next one.

03:21.410 --> 03:24.413
♪ lively theme song playing ♪

03:24.413 --> 03:27.416
♪ vocalizing ♪

04:09.499 --> 04:11.710
[door opens]
[footsteps]

04:11.710 --> 04:15.214
♪ soft music playing ♪

04:26.934 --> 04:28.435
♪

04:29.520 --> 04:31.647
Joy, can you come in here, please?

04:32.981 --> 04:36.944
♪ rapidly hums <i>Wedding March ♪</i>

04:36.944 --> 04:40.364
<i>♪ Here comes the bride,
all dressed in white ♪</i>

04:40.364 --> 04:43.575
<i>♪ She's wearing a thong,
we hope that's not wrong ♪</i>

04:43.575 --> 04:45.369
<i>♪ We're late to taste ♪</i>

04:45.369 --> 04:48.747
<i>♪ Magnolia Bakery wedding cakes ♪</i>

04:48.747 --> 04:50.040
[both laughing]

04:50.040 --> 04:51.416
[playful yelp]

04:51.416 --> 04:54.294
- [laughs] Charlie, you ready to go?
- Yeah!

04:54.294 --> 04:55.587
Yeah. Hey, Joy!

04:55.587 --> 04:58.340
Hey, this, uh, Ruby Strippers lipstick?

04:58.340 --> 04:59.883
- Uh-huh.
- Did I tell you where we found it?

04:59.883 --> 05:01.301
It was backstage.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.345
- Okay...
- Yeah. It was--

05:03.345 --> 05:05.264
[through kisses]
<i>in Ben's dressing room to be exact.</i>

05:05.264 --> 05:07.349
<i>I mean, any clue
how that would've gotten there?</i>

05:07.349 --> 05:09.893
[sighs] Hey, Brazzos.

05:09.893 --> 05:11.937
[tough guy accent]
<i>Hang up your badge, okay?</i>

05:11.937 --> 05:14.481
<i>We're on hiatus.</i>

05:14.481 --> 05:16.233
<i>Remember?</i> [blows]

05:16.984 --> 05:17.985
[Joy laughs]

05:17.985 --> 05:20.779
Yeah, b-but just for my case files,
how would it have gotten there?

05:20.779 --> 05:23.782
- [aquarium bubbling]
- Seriously, President McKinley?

05:23.782 --> 05:27.035
<i>This</i> is your last strike!

05:27.035 --> 05:28.161
President McKinley?

05:28.161 --> 05:30.497
I always wanted to be friends
with a president,

05:30.497 --> 05:33.208
but this one's an asshole.

05:33.208 --> 05:36.920
You think I don't see what you're doing,
you slimy-finned terrorist?

05:36.920 --> 05:39.214
I do not tolerate bullies.
[splashing]

05:39.214 --> 05:41.842
You're in solitary, POTUS.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.260
[Joy chuckles]

05:45.554 --> 05:46.930
Joy,

05:46.930 --> 05:50.017
someone wrote a threatening message
on Ben's mirror with this.

05:50.893 --> 05:52.186
Do you know anything about that?

05:52.186 --> 05:53.187
♪

05:53.187 --> 05:55.564
Charles-Haden Savage.

05:56.398 --> 05:59.985
Do you honestly think
I had something to do with Ben's death?

05:59.985 --> 06:01.403
[knocking on door]

06:07.576 --> 06:09.578
- Whoa!
- Happy engagement!

06:09.578 --> 06:10.579
[both laugh]
CHARLES: Ow!

06:11.330 --> 06:13.999
Whoa! Charles, you gotta
get you to my Pilates guy.

06:13.999 --> 06:15.501
And my face guy.

06:15.501 --> 06:17.711
You got a little Shar-Pei action
going on there.

06:18.795 --> 06:19.880
[soft laugh]

06:19.880 --> 06:22.257
- Sazzmatazz!
- Almond Joy!

06:22.257 --> 06:24.301
BOTH:
Oh...

06:24.301 --> 06:26.762
You know, they say a gift given in love

06:26.762 --> 06:29.598
has the power to wipe away
<i>any</i> storm brewing.

06:29.598 --> 06:31.225
It's an 18-piece fondue set.

06:31.225 --> 06:34.436
- Oh, thank you.
- Aw, we missed ya, Sazzmanian Devil.

06:34.436 --> 06:36.813
Well, Wile E. Joy-ote,

06:36.813 --> 06:38.982
apparently not enough
for your new fiancé

06:38.982 --> 06:41.443
to make me his understudy in the play.

06:41.443 --> 06:43.570
- Oh, well, I--
- I'm over it.

06:43.570 --> 06:46.156
I'm doing stunts for Bakula
next week in LA.

06:46.156 --> 06:47.866
Are you cheating on me with Scott?!

06:48.742 --> 06:49.743
JOY:
Ooh.

06:50.327 --> 06:51.537
Woo!

06:51.537 --> 06:53.413
Do send Scotty my love.
[Charles laughs]

06:53.413 --> 06:55.582
I miss his faith in me.

06:55.582 --> 06:58.544
He never accuses me of horrible things.

06:59.086 --> 07:00.295
You know what, Charles?

07:00.295 --> 07:02.464
You trust my palate, right?

07:02.464 --> 07:05.217
I think that, uh, I can taste test
these cakes on my own.

07:05.926 --> 07:07.427
You stay here with Sazz.

07:07.970 --> 07:10.472
Maybe she wants to be <i>interrogated.</i>

07:11.932 --> 07:13.809
- [slams door]
- Ooh.

07:15.018 --> 07:17.521
Okay, talk to mama.

07:18.897 --> 07:21.024
[metal rattling]
[exhales, snorts]

07:22.317 --> 07:23.318
[spritz]

07:25.529 --> 07:27.531
[knocking]
[door unlocks]

07:27.531 --> 07:30.993
- [sighs] Oh! Oliver, you're here.
- Ah.

07:30.993 --> 07:33.620
- I thought I heard someone.
- You're a vision.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.914
- [nervous chuckle]
- Well... [nervous chuckle]

07:35.914 --> 07:38.083
<i>Enchanté, ma chérie.</i>
[oven timer dings]

07:38.083 --> 07:40.252
Oh. Welcome to my slice of New York.

07:40.252 --> 07:42.629
It's itty-bitty,
but it's, you know, it's...

07:42.629 --> 07:43.630
[oven door squeaks]

07:43.630 --> 07:45.465
- Oh! Mm-hmm.
- Art!

07:45.465 --> 07:47.467
It's art.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.720
[Loretta sighs]
Who are you?

07:50.387 --> 07:53.348
[sighs] I'm a woman
with a broken microwave.

07:53.348 --> 07:57.060
Which is why I'm forced to
[coughs] improvise with this...

07:57.060 --> 08:00.397
prehistoric broiler
that I never use! [laughs]

08:00.397 --> 08:02.107
You do like pork chops though, don't you?

08:02.107 --> 08:05.402
Oh, sure. Love solid food. Love...

08:06.320 --> 08:08.030
chewing on a chop.
[both laugh]

08:08.030 --> 08:09.740
[coughing] Yeah.

08:09.740 --> 08:12.492
You know, I zap a perfectly pink one
in my microwave.

08:12.492 --> 08:15.287
- Yeah? Mm...
- But it's broken and now my timing,

08:15.287 --> 08:17.873
- the temperature, all thrown off.
- C-Can I assist?

08:17.873 --> 08:20.584
No, just, uh, pop a squat, kumquat.

08:20.584 --> 08:21.752
- [giggles]
- Oh.

08:23.504 --> 08:24.505
[beep]

08:24.505 --> 08:25.964
So... unique.

08:25.964 --> 08:27.424
[pots clanging]

08:27.424 --> 08:29.218
What's this fun thing?

08:29.218 --> 08:31.512
- Oh no! Don't open that! Don't do that!
- Oh!

08:31.512 --> 08:32.804
[Oliver laughs nervously]

08:32.804 --> 08:34.806
S... I'm sorry. I didn't...

08:35.599 --> 08:37.559
Didn't mean to jump the gun.

08:37.559 --> 08:39.561
♪

08:39.561 --> 08:41.980
Dinner before dessert, I always say.

08:43.065 --> 08:44.316
Oh. [nervous laugh]

08:44.316 --> 08:47.319
[restaurant chatter]

08:47.319 --> 08:50.322
♪ soft piano playing ♪

08:51.406 --> 08:52.658
There you are.

08:53.408 --> 08:55.410
- Hi.
- Hi.

08:55.410 --> 08:56.662
You look fantastic.

08:57.913 --> 09:00.499
Thanks. You also look, um...

09:00.499 --> 09:02.501
Well, you know, I clean up.

09:04.545 --> 09:07.214
So, we're here because your suspect

09:07.214 --> 09:08.715
likes swanky piano bars?

09:08.715 --> 09:10.676
Oh, I already ordered us
some, uh, bites.

09:10.676 --> 09:12.094
I wasn't sure what your drink was.

09:12.094 --> 09:13.846
EMCEE: Ladies and gentlemen,
let's give a warm welcome...

09:13.846 --> 09:17.057
Wait, what's going on?
Wh-Where's your lead?

09:17.057 --> 09:18.976
- [applause, cheering]
- [over microphone] <i>Hey, cool cats.</i>

09:18.976 --> 09:21.520
<i>I'm Johnny Jay,
and I'm gonna sing for you tonight.</i>

09:21.520 --> 09:23.814
♪ jaunty piano tune begins ♪

09:23.814 --> 09:27.150
<i>♪ Just a song at twilight ♪</i>

09:27.150 --> 09:29.987
<i>♪ When the lights are low ♪</i>

09:30.404 --> 09:31.905
Jonathan?

09:31.905 --> 09:34.449
Howard's sweet boyfriend is your guy?

09:34.449 --> 09:37.035
Well, he <i>was.</i>
I thought he was a great suspect.

09:37.035 --> 09:38.245
Ben's understudy?

09:38.245 --> 09:40.581
Who else had more to gain
from him dying, you know?

09:40.581 --> 09:42.624
But, I've been following him
around for a while now,

09:42.624 --> 09:45.419
and all I could find out was that
he volunteers with Broadway Cares

09:45.419 --> 09:48.088
and has this fantastic weekly cabaret set.

09:48.088 --> 09:49.798
- You've gotta be kidding me.
- No, seriously.

09:49.798 --> 09:53.010
He did, uh, <i>Somewhere Over The Rainbow</i>
last week. I actually wept.

09:53.010 --> 09:56.346
Let me get this straight.
You texted me saying you have a lead.

09:56.346 --> 09:58.223
I text you saying "tell me more."

09:58.223 --> 09:59.933
You say "meet me here,"
I'm here,

09:59.933 --> 10:02.269
and now you're telling me
you don't have a lead.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.688
You're just Jonathan's
biggest cabaret fan.

10:04.688 --> 10:08.525
And now, I am on a date
with that cute girl from the armoire.

10:08.525 --> 10:10.527
♪ piano continues ♪

10:10.527 --> 10:13.780
Okay, yes, I got creative.
Is that okay?

10:15.157 --> 10:17.367
Mezcal old-fashioned.

10:17.367 --> 10:19.119
Is my drink.

10:19.661 --> 10:21.163
That I'm now gonna need.

10:21.163 --> 10:22.664
WAITER:
Yes, ma'am.

10:23.248 --> 10:24.249
[Tobert sighs]

10:27.961 --> 10:30.464
[aquarium bubbling]
SAZZ: Let's unpack what just happened.

10:30.464 --> 10:33.133
Safe space.
Well, safe-ish. [laughs]

10:33.133 --> 10:34.468
This is the Arconia.

10:34.468 --> 10:36.887
Oh, abnormal amount
of death in this place.

10:36.887 --> 10:40.265
By the way, are we sure
that the killer was after Ben,

10:40.265 --> 10:42.267
- and not you, Charles?
- What?

10:42.267 --> 10:44.520
Well, I've been getting some vibes.

10:44.520 --> 10:46.271
I also have my ham radio,

10:46.271 --> 10:49.858
and there's chatter of people
wishing it was <i>you</i> instead of Ben.

10:49.858 --> 10:52.569
- Me?!
- Anywhos,

10:52.569 --> 10:54.238
what's going on with Joy?

10:54.238 --> 10:56.156
And have you talked
to a therapist about it?

10:56.156 --> 10:58.575
- I don't have a therapist.
- I know you don't.

10:58.575 --> 11:01.537
It was always worth me asking,
'cause that big white head of yours?

11:01.537 --> 11:03.705
[laughs] Could use a good shrinking.

11:03.705 --> 11:06.041
Ah, Jan and I laugh about that.

11:06.041 --> 11:07.042
- Jan?
- Whoa!

11:07.042 --> 11:09.086
I should've trigger-warned. Yes, yes.

11:09.086 --> 11:12.172
I have continued to see Jan, yes.

11:12.172 --> 11:14.216
As in dating? She's a murderer.

11:14.216 --> 11:15.425
Yeah.

11:15.425 --> 11:18.053
You know, I guess it's the,
uh, stuntwoman in me.

11:18.053 --> 11:20.931
I got the hots for danger. [soft laugh]

11:20.931 --> 11:23.767
Anyway, it's a bit hard behind plexiglass.

11:23.767 --> 11:26.520
Or, as Jan calls it, sexi-glass.

11:27.563 --> 11:30.607
There's only so much you can do
with a raised eyebrow,

11:30.607 --> 11:33.735
a wet lip, and a sliver of tit.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.946
God, you are tense, man.

11:35.946 --> 11:37.197
Sazz.

11:37.739 --> 11:40.033
- I'm worried that Joy is another killer.
- What?!

11:40.033 --> 11:41.743
Joy?

11:41.743 --> 11:43.537
We've known her for decades.

11:43.537 --> 11:45.080
No, no, no, no, no.

11:45.080 --> 11:48.125
You've got the case
and the engagement all mushed up.

11:48.125 --> 11:50.043
You have to prove to yourself
Joy's not a murderer,

11:50.043 --> 11:51.336
so you can go ahead with the wedding.

11:51.336 --> 11:54.089
No. I have to prove
Joy isn't a murderer,

11:54.089 --> 11:55.465
so I can break up with her

11:55.465 --> 11:57.843
and not be in fear for my life
like I was with Jan!

11:57.843 --> 12:01.305
Charles, you are suffering from MGDS:

12:01.305 --> 12:04.683
Murderous Girlfriend Derangement Syndrome.

12:04.683 --> 12:06.852
It's rare. I invented it.

12:06.852 --> 12:09.229
But it also means I know the treatment.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.399
Whoa. You know you got
the Rolls Royce of fish tanks here.

12:12.399 --> 12:15.360
♪

12:16.945 --> 12:18.822
We're gonna play a game.

12:20.532 --> 12:22.451
Cheers.

12:22.451 --> 12:24.286
Cheers.
[glasses clink]

12:24.286 --> 12:26.830
So glad we didn't waste our money
going to Le Cirque.

12:27.247 --> 12:29.708
- [both laugh]
- Yeah.

12:29.708 --> 12:31.001
Hm...

12:31.001 --> 12:33.253
Mm. [sighs]

12:34.796 --> 12:36.507
LORETTA: Mm...
[sighs]

12:40.093 --> 12:41.136
[Oliver grunts]

12:42.095 --> 12:45.432
It's so solid.
So fully formed, you know?

12:45.432 --> 12:47.726
- Damn broiler. I'm just--
- No, it's just...

12:47.726 --> 12:49.770
Oh, what the hell, I'm just gonna...

12:49.770 --> 12:52.147
Look at this. [loud grunt]
That's what I'm gonna...

12:52.147 --> 12:54.107
- Well...
- Wh-Why cut it?

12:54.107 --> 12:55.108
Why not?

12:55.108 --> 12:56.944
[crunching]
[loud grunt]

12:58.070 --> 13:00.322
So good. [smacks lips]

13:01.365 --> 13:03.784
♪

13:03.784 --> 13:05.494
[Oliver sighs]

13:06.161 --> 13:07.996
- Oh, my God!
- Oh!

13:07.996 --> 13:09.748
So sorry!
[both gasp]

13:09.748 --> 13:12.084
Is that mine?!
LORETTA: Oh no, I'm so mortified!

13:12.084 --> 13:13.961
Let me get you some ice or something.

13:13.961 --> 13:17.881
No, no, no, I don't--
I-I actually don't feel anything...

13:17.881 --> 13:19.466
- You sure?
- No.

13:21.301 --> 13:22.803
Oh God.

13:23.679 --> 13:25.973
[gasps]
[weak whistling]

13:25.973 --> 13:28.934
[both laugh]

13:28.934 --> 13:30.269
[snorts]

13:30.269 --> 13:32.980
[Oliver groans]
I love that little snort you do.

13:32.980 --> 13:35.232
[laughs] You do?
LORETTA: Yeah,

13:35.232 --> 13:38.235
I do. [laughs]
You're like an adorable little piglet.

13:38.235 --> 13:41.738
[Loretta snorting]
[awkward laugh]

13:41.738 --> 13:44.867
I played a pig
in the cruise ship production

13:44.867 --> 13:47.244
of <i>Charlotte's Web</i> once, in my 30s,

13:47.244 --> 13:50.205
but I think I really honed my snort

13:50.205 --> 13:53.709
when I played Snowball
in a black box production

13:53.709 --> 13:55.627
of, um, <i>Animal Farm.</i>

13:55.627 --> 13:57.421
How many pigs have you played?

13:57.421 --> 13:59.548
[imitating pig]
<i>I don't know.</i> [oinking]

13:59.548 --> 14:01.466
- [laughing]
- Come on.

14:01.466 --> 14:04.678
Fucking pigs. Fucking pi--

14:04.678 --> 14:07.681
Hey, you know who was
a real fucking pig? [laughs]

14:08.849 --> 14:10.100
Ben Glenroy.

14:10.100 --> 14:12.186
[laughs, clears throat]

14:12.186 --> 14:13.604
Let's toast to him.

14:14.688 --> 14:16.190
♪

14:20.277 --> 14:22.696
- What's the matter?
- N-Nothing.

14:22.696 --> 14:23.739
You just went white.

14:23.739 --> 14:26.742
No, no, no, nothing.
I just, um, it's just those words.

14:27.868 --> 14:29.912
Did you ever tell Ben that?

14:29.912 --> 14:32.664
That he was a, how'd you put it,
a fucking pig?

14:32.664 --> 14:35.584
Let's not talk about Ben now. I mean...

14:35.584 --> 14:38.295
Yes! No, no, no. No, no, no, n--

14:38.295 --> 14:41.465
No more Ben talk. No more Ben. No Ben.

14:41.465 --> 14:42.716
Just...

14:44.718 --> 14:47.721
- [clears throat]
- Did I just make things weird?

14:47.721 --> 14:50.516
- No! No, no, no. No. Just...
- Yes.

14:50.974 --> 14:54.269
You poor thing. Your tooth.

14:57.397 --> 14:58.649
Do you trust me?

14:58.649 --> 15:00.067
Huh?

15:00.692 --> 15:02.736
Wanna get outta here?

15:04.238 --> 15:07.741
I know just the place for this.

15:07.741 --> 15:11.245
♪ upbeat piano playing ♪

15:14.081 --> 15:17.793
<i>♪ Meet me tonight in dreamland ♪</i>

15:17.793 --> 15:21.129
Mm! Okay,
so your drink of choice, mezcal.

15:21.129 --> 15:24.633
Your weather of choice, rain.
And your favorite time of day, night.

15:24.633 --> 15:26.927
Not exactly a fount of information,
are you?

15:26.927 --> 15:29.638
Hey, you got me here
under false pretenses.

15:29.638 --> 15:31.181
I'm making you work for it.
[laughs]

15:31.181 --> 15:35.102
That's fair. So, um,
Oliver and Charles, what is that deal?

15:35.102 --> 15:37.271
Are they, like, your dads, your patrons,

15:37.271 --> 15:39.231
your volunteer work, what?
[laughs]

15:39.231 --> 15:42.192
No! They're... my best buds.

15:42.192 --> 15:44.194
Okay. That's rad.

15:45.571 --> 15:46.989
But, like, what do you talk about?

15:46.989 --> 15:48.824
Murder, mostly.

15:48.824 --> 15:51.827
And how to connect to Bluetooth.
We talk about that a lot.

15:51.827 --> 15:54.037
So what do you say?
Have I earned a second round?

15:55.205 --> 15:57.207
- WAITER: Yes, ma'am?
- Two more, please.

15:57.207 --> 15:58.458
WAITER:
Coming right up.

15:59.459 --> 16:02.546
Alright, so who's in your crew?
And wildlife doesn't count.

16:02.546 --> 16:04.965
Honestly, it's really tough
to stay in contact

16:04.965 --> 16:06.592
with anybody
when you're constantly traveling.

16:07.718 --> 16:11.430
And if you don't have a partner
to ground you, put down roots...

16:13.849 --> 16:15.726
Is that something you want?

16:16.685 --> 16:18.270
I think about it.

16:19.229 --> 16:22.107
SAZZ:
<i>Welcome to "Commit Or Be Committed!"</i>

16:22.107 --> 16:24.401
And tonight's contestants are me,

16:24.401 --> 16:26.111
in the role of Joy Payne,

16:26.111 --> 16:27.863
makeup artist to the stars.

16:27.863 --> 16:30.949
And playing opposite Joy,
you know him as Brazzos,

16:30.949 --> 16:33.952
- Charles-Haden Savage!
- Hey. [chuckles]

16:34.745 --> 16:37.164
Our first category...

16:37.164 --> 16:40.083
is sexual relations.

16:40.083 --> 16:42.461
[whispers]
<i>Now, remember. I'm Joy.</i>

16:45.172 --> 16:47.382
[imitating Joy]
<i>I need sex twice a day,</i>

16:47.382 --> 16:49.468
<i>three times on weekends!</i>

16:52.387 --> 16:54.431
[imitates buzzer] Wrong answer!

16:54.431 --> 16:57.392
Nothing wrong with
a supercharged sex drive, Charles.

16:57.392 --> 17:01.021
Our next category is the future.

17:01.021 --> 17:03.190
[imitating Joy]
<i>You</i> are <i>my future.</i>

17:03.190 --> 17:06.818
<i>And I'll never, ever leave you, Charlie.
Ever!</i>

17:06.818 --> 17:09.530
<i>Never! Never ever!</i>

17:10.405 --> 17:13.617
[lights click]
Well! Our first green light.

17:13.617 --> 17:16.620
Alright. You're up. Dig deep.

17:17.287 --> 17:18.288
[sighs]

17:19.873 --> 17:23.669
Joy has been <i>this</i> close
to my face for 30-plus years,

17:23.669 --> 17:26.004
looking at every flaw and pore,

17:26.004 --> 17:28.757
and she still wants to jump my bones,
often twice a day.

17:28.757 --> 17:31.343
Now, isn't that the behavior
of a psychopath?

17:31.343 --> 17:34.680
Mm, sounds like the behavior of
someone who loves you for you.

17:34.680 --> 17:36.640
But I'm me.

17:36.640 --> 17:40.602
Look at me. Is this the face
of someone who deserves Joy?

17:40.602 --> 17:42.104
[click]
SAZZ: Ding, ding, ding, ding, ding!

17:42.104 --> 17:43.730
I think we have a diagnosis.

17:43.730 --> 17:45.357
Charles-Haden Savage,

17:45.357 --> 17:48.485
you're not afraid of uppercase "J" Joy.

17:48.485 --> 17:51.655
You're afraid of lowercase "j" joy.

17:51.655 --> 17:54.825
♪

17:54.825 --> 17:58.036
[aquarium bubbling]

17:58.745 --> 17:59.997
That's it.

18:01.081 --> 18:02.207
That's my problem.

18:02.207 --> 18:04.293
Now do you still think
she's capable of murder?

18:04.293 --> 18:06.086
No, I was crazy for thinking that.

18:06.086 --> 18:09.548
No, you're not that complex.
You do need to stop being a scaredy cat.

18:12.426 --> 18:14.553
[both trill lips, sigh]

18:14.553 --> 18:17.556
♪

18:19.474 --> 18:21.351
LORETTA: Whoa.

18:21.351 --> 18:23.061
[gasps]
[Oliver laughs]

18:23.061 --> 18:24.563
Wow!

18:24.980 --> 18:27.524
- Oh, my gosh.
- You know, it is truly amazing

18:27.524 --> 18:29.735
that you can charter a yacht

18:29.735 --> 18:32.029
in the greatest city on Earth
for four dollars.

18:32.029 --> 18:33.655
[laughs] Yeah.

18:33.655 --> 18:35.616
[laughs] Is there a destination?

18:35.616 --> 18:37.826
- The tropics?
- You'll see.

18:37.826 --> 18:39.077
[both laugh]

18:39.077 --> 18:40.287
Pick your poison.

18:40.287 --> 18:41.997
Poison?

18:43.081 --> 18:44.166
Or...

18:44.958 --> 18:47.044
Hoo-wee!

18:47.044 --> 18:49.463
Now, we're talking.
[Loretta giggles]

18:49.463 --> 18:52.049
- Look, that joint has purple rolling paper.
- I know.

18:52.049 --> 18:53.342
Groovy-doobie.

18:53.342 --> 18:54.968
[Indian accent]
<i>Do you doobie, baby?</i>

18:54.968 --> 18:57.054
[both laugh]

18:57.054 --> 19:00.307
My 12th roommate, Babette Claus,

19:00.307 --> 19:02.559
gave me this back in 1978.

19:02.559 --> 19:04.186
[soft laugh]

19:04.186 --> 19:06.563
- Wait, Babette? I-Is--
- Yeah.

19:07.397 --> 19:09.566
Is that the chorus girl
that got struck by lightning

19:09.566 --> 19:11.985
- skinny dipping in Central Park--
- Skinny dipping, Central Park Reservoir.

19:11.985 --> 19:15.113
- I know... Mm-hmm.
- Oh my-- Okay, this is... this is insane.

19:15.113 --> 19:18.951
I rolled 10 joints for Babette

19:18.951 --> 19:22.412
using a purple streamer
from Studio 54 that year.

19:23.247 --> 19:25.040
- At Grace Jones'--
- Her 30th birthday party!

19:25.040 --> 19:26.041
Yes!

19:26.041 --> 19:28.627
- I was at that party! Yes, I was!
- No, you were not.

19:28.627 --> 19:30.045
Oh, my God!

19:30.045 --> 19:33.257
That's the only time
I ever got in there. [laughs]

19:33.257 --> 19:36.510
This is ridic-- I can't believe this.
I think I rolled that joint.

19:37.302 --> 19:40.305
- Now, spark it, baby!
- Wow.

19:40.305 --> 19:42.057
[laughing]

19:42.057 --> 19:44.601
So I guess-- I guess we've been

19:44.601 --> 19:47.437
running in the same circles
for a long time.

19:48.689 --> 19:51.108
- Oh, yes.
- It's a shame our orbits never crossed.

19:51.650 --> 19:54.069
Well, I may not have been on your radar,

19:54.069 --> 19:57.364
but you were <i>certainly</i> on mine.
[exhales]

19:59.533 --> 20:02.661
I would've killed to be in
one of your productions but [sniffs]...

20:02.661 --> 20:06.623
something always happened to screw it up.

20:06.623 --> 20:09.585
Like my ponytail got stuck
in the subway doors once

20:09.585 --> 20:13.422
on the way to audition for your
<i>Merry Wives.</i>

20:13.422 --> 20:15.424
Oh, and then there was
the time Bernadette Peters

20:15.424 --> 20:18.302
gave me a bottled water
that was laced with Valium.

20:18.302 --> 20:20.596
And then I passed out in the waiting room,

20:20.596 --> 20:23.348
and I missed the chance
to be your Annie Oakley.

20:23.765 --> 20:25.726
You made that all up, didn't you?
[both laugh]

20:25.726 --> 20:27.561
[horn blares]
[both yelp]

20:27.561 --> 20:28.854
Oh Jesus.

20:28.854 --> 20:31.899
[horn continues]
Dear God. Oh my...

20:31.899 --> 20:32.941
Wow. [sniffs]

20:32.941 --> 20:34.943
Yeah, but you know,
it is always something

20:34.943 --> 20:38.780
just infuriatingly, um, banal.

20:39.406 --> 20:42.326
Like, "your accent is too authentic,"

20:42.326 --> 20:45.495
o-or, "casting doesn't like you,"
or-- I don't know.

20:45.996 --> 20:48.790
You know, when I was a kid,
they called me Lucky Durkin

20:49.333 --> 20:52.628
because I won the school raffle
four times.

20:54.004 --> 20:56.173
But, since then...

20:56.173 --> 20:59.426
[deep inhale, deep exhale]

20:59.426 --> 21:01.845
Some nickname that turned out to be.

21:02.888 --> 21:05.390
Maybe I'm just cursed. [weak laugh]

21:05.390 --> 21:06.850
[sighs]

21:06.850 --> 21:09.645
Or... it's probably...

21:10.062 --> 21:11.855
what I deserve.

21:11.855 --> 21:15.442
Oh, come on. What could you have done
to deserve being cursed?

21:18.195 --> 21:19.446
[sighs]

21:21.657 --> 21:23.534
Open your mouth.

21:23.534 --> 21:26.620
♪

21:28.539 --> 21:30.207
[exhales]

21:30.207 --> 21:31.458
[Oliver inhales]

21:31.458 --> 21:33.585
♪

21:35.003 --> 21:37.506
[gap whistling]
<i>That was super sexy.</i>

21:38.257 --> 21:40.259
Am I crazy? [laughs]

21:41.301 --> 21:42.678
I thi...

21:42.678 --> 21:45.556
I think the gap is handsome.

21:45.556 --> 21:48.767
Well, that might be
the 40-year-old weed taking effect,

21:48.767 --> 21:51.395
you know?
[both laugh]

21:51.770 --> 21:56.358
<i>♪ There let my dreams... ♪</i>

21:56.358 --> 22:02.114
<i>♪ Come true... ♪</i>

22:02.114 --> 22:04.950
[cheering and applause]

22:06.618 --> 22:09.538
God, I can't believe you ever thought
Jonathan was...

22:09.538 --> 22:11.540
<i>♪ A murdering man ♪</i>

22:11.540 --> 22:14.251
That's still not a song, but cute.

22:14.251 --> 22:18.172
So, what, you solved the first two murders
just on your first try, I presume?

22:18.172 --> 22:21.466
Yeah, totally.
Between me, Charles, and Oliver,

22:21.466 --> 22:23.719
it's just, like, a one-day process.

22:24.178 --> 22:27.639
Well, lucky for me,
this one's taking you a <i>little</i> bit longer.

22:27.639 --> 22:29.516
♪ soft piano playing ♪

22:29.516 --> 22:31.560
Oh, there's Jonathan again.

22:31.560 --> 22:34.563
[inaudible]

22:34.563 --> 22:35.939
Who's he hugging hello?

22:36.690 --> 22:39.651
No! Don't look. Don't draw attention.

22:40.736 --> 22:42.571
Could Jonathan be...

22:43.238 --> 22:45.741
No, he wouldn't cheat on Howard.

22:45.741 --> 22:47.618
With who? There's somebody?
Describe him.

22:47.618 --> 22:50.621
Well, he looks like
he should be in a limo.

22:50.621 --> 22:52.581
Rider or driver, I can't tell.

22:52.581 --> 22:54.166
That's your description?

22:54.166 --> 22:58.086
- He's wearing a red coat and a cap.
- Huh.

22:58.086 --> 23:01.340
MABEL: Oh, now Jonathan's
handing him an envelope,

23:01.340 --> 23:04.510
and the guy is giving him a slip of paper?

23:04.510 --> 23:06.136
Okay, this is killing me.
I'm just gonna come to that side,

23:06.136 --> 23:07.596
- and we can both be watching.
- No!

23:07.596 --> 23:09.723
[glasses shatter]
[patrons gasp]

23:09.723 --> 23:12.351
- Sorry! Sorry. You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

23:12.351 --> 23:14.269
I think we should stay
down here for a second.

23:14.269 --> 23:15.812
Yeah.

23:15.812 --> 23:17.189
- Okay, I gotta look.
- No, no, no, don't.

23:17.189 --> 23:18.774
You look, he'll definitely see you.

23:18.774 --> 23:20.859
I mean, unless we do the classic move

23:20.859 --> 23:23.487
from the secret spy movies
where the target looks,

23:23.487 --> 23:25.822
and just sees two unassuming
secret agents making out.

23:26.281 --> 23:27.991
Yeah, I don't think
that'll be necessary.

23:27.991 --> 23:29.910
- They didn't see us.
- Well.

23:29.910 --> 23:32.246
♪

23:35.749 --> 23:37.709
Ah, we should've done the kissing thing.

23:43.340 --> 23:44.842
What the hell?

23:44.842 --> 23:48.345
We need to figure out
who this guy in the cap is.

23:48.345 --> 23:50.138
Actually, I think I do know that guy.

23:50.138 --> 23:52.057
♪

23:55.060 --> 23:57.521
[water lapping]
LORETTA: We were very tired.

23:57.521 --> 23:59.773
We were very merry.

23:59.773 --> 24:03.360
We had gone back and forth
all night on the ferry.

24:03.360 --> 24:04.361
[Oliver chuckles]

24:04.361 --> 24:06.363
This is really...

24:07.906 --> 24:09.741
really nice.

24:09.741 --> 24:11.869
It is.
[distant ship horn]

24:13.287 --> 24:16.290
[sighs] I'm sorry about earlier.

24:17.624 --> 24:19.418
At my place.

24:19.418 --> 24:21.753
I didn't mean to get weird about Ben.

24:21.753 --> 24:25.132
I just had an idea about tonight

24:25.132 --> 24:29.094
and talking about a dead person
just didn't feel like the mood.

24:29.636 --> 24:32.639
Well, it-it-it's alright
to talk about him.

24:33.432 --> 24:36.935
You know, I mean it-it's quite
the thing we all went through.

24:36.935 --> 24:38.353
- Yeah.
- It's just...

24:38.353 --> 24:40.856
that was a very...
[Loretta sighs]

24:40.856 --> 24:43.567
specific turn of phrase you used.

24:43.567 --> 24:45.110
"Fucking pig."

24:45.110 --> 24:47.863
[laughs] Yeah, shit, because I...

24:47.863 --> 24:50.991
I did call him that. [sighs]

24:50.991 --> 24:52.576
♪

24:52.576 --> 24:53.577
We had a fight.

24:53.577 --> 24:55.621
[sniffles] Yeah.

24:55.621 --> 24:58.248
Just half an hour
before he went on the stage that night.

24:58.248 --> 24:59.583
[Ben struggling]
[Loretta screams]

24:59.583 --> 25:02.461
He said that I was obsessed with him,

25:02.461 --> 25:06.215
and that, uh, I had
wormed my way into the show

25:06.715 --> 25:10.552
and that he didn't really want
to share the stage with a no-name.

25:11.011 --> 25:14.473
So, I-- Yeah, I snapped.

25:14.473 --> 25:16.183
"You fucking pig."

25:16.183 --> 25:18.185
[struggling]
Let go of me, you fucking pig!

25:18.185 --> 25:19.436
[sighs]

25:21.146 --> 25:23.649
The last thing I said to him...

25:24.942 --> 25:27.444
before he collapsed. Ugh.

25:29.321 --> 25:30.822
But I was...

25:31.281 --> 25:34.743
far from the only person in that theater
who felt that way about him.

25:34.743 --> 25:37.246
He was an asshole to everybody.

25:38.747 --> 25:40.499
Even his [sighs]...

25:40.499 --> 25:44.044
kind-hearted brother.

25:47.506 --> 25:49.633
♪

25:49.633 --> 25:52.845
But I'm really sorry you didn't get
your opening night.

25:54.972 --> 25:57.224
Well, I'm sorry he was terrible to you.

25:59.101 --> 26:00.811
I adore you,

26:00.811 --> 26:02.771
Loretta Lucky Durkin,

26:02.771 --> 26:05.524
and everything about you.

26:05.524 --> 26:08.402
Apart from that pork chop.
I'll never forgive you for that.

26:08.402 --> 26:12.322
[both laugh, sigh]

26:14.116 --> 26:15.117
[quiet gasp]

26:15.826 --> 26:17.202
Here we are.

26:17.202 --> 26:20.205
This is why I brought you
out on the ferry!

26:20.205 --> 26:22.040
What?

26:22.040 --> 26:23.834
Family tradition.

26:23.834 --> 26:27.045
When I was a girl,
whenever I lost a tooth,

26:27.045 --> 26:30.632
my mom would take me out
on the Mississippi River,

26:30.632 --> 26:32.968
on the ferry boat and

26:32.968 --> 26:35.095
when we got underneath a bridge,

26:35.095 --> 26:38.140
we'd throw the tooth overboard

26:38.140 --> 26:39.474
and make a wish.

26:39.975 --> 26:41.727
The Tooth Fairy can swim?

26:44.062 --> 26:45.772
- It's--
- Tooth <i>ferry</i>.

26:45.772 --> 26:47.357
- Tooth ferry!
- Yeah.

26:47.357 --> 26:50.736
- Okay, okay.
- I know, it's really corny.

26:50.736 --> 26:52.654
Oh, I-I'm a...

26:52.654 --> 26:55.657
- big fan of corny.
- Well, here's your tooth.

26:55.657 --> 26:58.035
Right. Alright.

26:58.035 --> 27:01.288
♪

27:01.288 --> 27:01.955
[quiet splash]

27:03.290 --> 27:06.293
♪ vocalizing ♪

27:06.293 --> 27:08.086
What'd you wish for?

27:16.553 --> 27:19.556
♪ gentle crescendo ♪

27:26.396 --> 27:29.399
♪ music fades ♪

27:29.399 --> 27:31.610
So who was he?

27:31.610 --> 27:34.738
That was-- Thank you.
That was Ben's private doctor.

27:34.738 --> 27:36.490
One of those, uh, celebrity concierge,

27:36.490 --> 27:38.617
anything-you-need
prescription-filler types.

27:38.617 --> 27:40.827
He's actually come to see Ben
a few times this past year.

27:40.827 --> 27:42.663
Huh. You know what for?

27:42.663 --> 27:45.749
Uh, they never let me in the room.
I just know they call him Dr. C.

27:45.749 --> 27:48.001
Great, that's a perfect combination

27:48.001 --> 27:50.420
of mysterious and un-Googleable.

27:51.797 --> 27:54.007
But what was he talking
to Jonathan about?

27:54.007 --> 27:57.052
And if Jonathan was
paying him for something--

27:57.052 --> 27:59.137
You are so cute when you theorize.

28:02.391 --> 28:03.892
We should get outta here.

28:10.774 --> 28:13.277
Hey! I'm sorry you missed Sazz.

28:13.277 --> 28:14.987
She asked me to give you
a playful punch on the arm,

28:14.987 --> 28:17.322
but I don't wanna do that.
How'd the tasting go?

28:17.322 --> 28:18.949
I brought back 20 samples,

28:18.949 --> 28:21.743
so I wouldn't accidentally leave
a particular flavor behind

28:21.743 --> 28:24.621
and have you give me
the third degree about it.

28:24.621 --> 28:26.081
Oh, about that.

28:26.081 --> 28:28.166
I-I'm sorry I gave you a hard time
about the lipstick.

28:31.044 --> 28:32.045
[sighs]

28:32.045 --> 28:34.256
I was backstage on opening night.

28:34.256 --> 28:35.632
Oh?

28:35.632 --> 28:37.843
Howard summoned me back there in a panic

28:37.843 --> 28:41.013
because Ben had a cosmetic emergency.

28:41.013 --> 28:44.141
I don't know, I guess
somebody hit him in the face,

28:44.141 --> 28:45.601
and left a big red mark,

28:45.601 --> 28:48.604
- and it needed covering, which I did.
- Oh, wow.

28:48.604 --> 28:52.065
I'm guessing that my lipstick fell out
of my clutch when I was back there.

28:55.611 --> 28:57.613
But I didn't write on his mirror

28:57.613 --> 29:00.449
because I didn't kill Ben, Charlie.

29:01.074 --> 29:03.368
Well, here's one I never told anyone.

29:03.368 --> 29:06.914
I may, uh... probably,

29:06.914 --> 29:09.374
have been the person who hit Ben.

29:10.167 --> 29:12.961
- [struggling]
- [screams] Let go of me, you fucking pig!

29:12.961 --> 29:14.171
What the hell's going on?

29:14.171 --> 29:16.256
- LORETTA: He attacked me!
- No, I didn't--

29:16.256 --> 29:18.550
We were rehearsing.
Stay out of it, fuckbag!

29:18.550 --> 29:19.551
CHARLES:
Hey!

29:19.551 --> 29:21.845
[Charles grunts]
[Loretta gasps]

29:21.845 --> 29:25.098
Wait, <i>you</i> hit Ben? The night he died?

29:25.974 --> 29:27.809
And yet, for some reason,

29:27.809 --> 29:30.395
you've been thinking that
<i>I</i> could be the killer?

29:30.395 --> 29:31.855
Wh-- For how long?

29:31.855 --> 29:33.232
- Oh, not long at all.
- Oh.

29:33.232 --> 29:36.735
I mean, at first, I was like,
"Joy? My Joy? No way!"

29:36.735 --> 29:38.946
But then,
Oliver and Mabel weren't so sure.

29:38.946 --> 29:42.157
Wh-- You talked about this
with everyone else except me?

29:42.157 --> 29:45.035
And you still proposed thinking all this?

29:45.035 --> 29:47.829
[nervous laugh]
Well, you know, funny story.

29:47.829 --> 29:50.082
That was actually an accident.

29:50.082 --> 29:51.250
Accident?

29:51.250 --> 29:53.669
Well... [stammering]

29:53.669 --> 29:56.588
No. Not a-- I mean, it <i>was</i>, but then--

29:56.588 --> 29:58.632
You didn't <i>mean</i> to propose to me?

29:58.632 --> 30:00.384
No, I didn't.

30:00.384 --> 30:01.593
What?

30:01.593 --> 30:04.263
Wow. Okay.

30:04.263 --> 30:05.514
Gut punch.

30:05.514 --> 30:07.891
♪

30:07.891 --> 30:09.393
So...

30:11.144 --> 30:12.646
But...

30:16.149 --> 30:18.151
Do you wanna marry me now?

30:18.151 --> 30:21.071
I do! And it was great
that you left me with Sazz

30:21.071 --> 30:24.157
because she did this thing
with the fish tank, and a quiz.

30:24.157 --> 30:26.827
And it was like, uh,
"Is Joy a nymphomaniac?"

30:26.827 --> 30:28.912
Do you hear yourself right now?

30:28.912 --> 30:33.125
I think of all the years of you
in my makeup chair, Charlie.

30:33.125 --> 30:34.376
Joking.

30:35.419 --> 30:37.796
Little winks in the mirror.

30:37.796 --> 30:39.965
That kick in your step when you hopped up,

30:39.965 --> 30:42.301
looking good to go to the set.

30:42.301 --> 30:45.679
I always thought we had
something special, Charlie!

30:45.679 --> 30:47.931
So I looked past all the stuff.

30:47.931 --> 30:50.100
Your ego, your self-absorption,

30:50.100 --> 30:52.269
your psoriasis elbows.

30:52.269 --> 30:54.813
- You gave me a cream--
- It's not working!

30:55.397 --> 30:57.107
You know, Charlie,

30:57.107 --> 30:59.943
I've been trying to have an open dialogue

30:59.943 --> 31:01.945
about what we both want.

31:03.322 --> 31:06.325
But I'm kidding myself
to think you're <i>really</i> ready

31:06.325 --> 31:09.828
to open up to a woman as open as I am.

31:09.828 --> 31:12.706
I tried telling myself
you're gonna change,

31:12.706 --> 31:15.125
but I think it might be too late for you.

31:15.125 --> 31:16.710
No.

31:16.710 --> 31:19.671
It's not too late
because I have realized

31:19.671 --> 31:21.882
you are Joy...

31:21.882 --> 31:23.675
and <i>joy.</i>

31:23.675 --> 31:26.053
And I can embrace both of you.

31:26.053 --> 31:28.180
And I want to, Joy.

31:28.180 --> 31:30.599
I do. I do.

31:30.599 --> 31:32.518
♪

31:35.896 --> 31:37.231
Embrace this.

31:38.690 --> 31:39.691
[plate clatters]

31:40.817 --> 31:42.819
The engagement's off.

31:48.075 --> 31:50.285
[door opens, slams shut]

31:52.913 --> 31:53.914
[door shuts]
[lights click]

31:56.208 --> 31:58.710
Only two other men
have seen this before.

31:58.710 --> 32:00.712
♪

32:02.464 --> 32:04.800
TOBERT: I was pretty confident
going into tonight,

32:04.800 --> 32:08.136
but I did not expect to get
all the way to the Murder Board.

32:08.679 --> 32:11.765
- Wow, really? [laughs]
- Due diligence.

32:11.765 --> 32:13.767
You really know how
to make a guy feel special.

32:14.726 --> 32:16.687
- May I?
- Uh, I...

32:16.687 --> 32:18.313
don't know.
I'm worried about your handwriting.

32:18.313 --> 32:19.523
You shouldn't be.

32:21.483 --> 32:22.484
MABEL: Well...

32:22.484 --> 32:23.652
♪

32:27.906 --> 32:30.576
Look at us.
Real-life Rizzoli and Isles over here.

32:31.743 --> 32:33.161
What are you doing?

32:33.161 --> 32:34.663
Following the lead.

32:40.377 --> 32:43.380
♪

32:47.342 --> 32:50.345
[distant siren]

32:53.223 --> 32:56.685
I may not be good at dinner...

32:56.685 --> 33:00.397
But you excel at dessert.
[soft laugh]

33:03.901 --> 33:05.611
♪

33:05.611 --> 33:07.112
[both moan softly]

33:07.112 --> 33:09.823
Shall I draw us a bath?

33:10.365 --> 33:12.367
- OLIVER: You have one in here?
- Well, it's...

33:13.327 --> 33:16.455
more of a glorified barrel.
[both laugh]

33:16.455 --> 33:18.165
OLIVER:
Sounds cozy-wozy.

33:18.165 --> 33:21.168
[Loretta sighs, groans]

33:25.047 --> 33:27.549
[bathroom door opens, shuts]

33:28.675 --> 33:30.677
[water runs]

33:30.677 --> 33:33.680
♪

33:39.478 --> 33:41.980
JOY: <i>I will say
one other thing about love.</i>

33:42.731 --> 33:44.274
<i>There are times</i>

33:44.274 --> 33:47.528
<i>when you've been totally blinded</i>

33:47.528 --> 33:50.531
<i>by the mirage of your own desires.</i>

33:50.531 --> 33:51.949
Hm.

33:55.953 --> 33:58.956
♪ vocalizing ♪

34:11.218 --> 34:14.888
JOY: <i>And when the truth
of who you gave your heart to,</i>

34:14.888 --> 34:17.599
<i>of who they really are</i>

34:17.599 --> 34:20.727
<i>is suddenly staring you right in the face?</i>

34:20.727 --> 34:22.479
♪

34:22.479 --> 34:25.899
<i>It might be a sign that things
just aren't meant to be.</i>

34:27.067 --> 34:28.235
<i>Or worse.</i>

34:29.444 --> 34:33.073
♪

34:38.996 --> 34:39.997
LORETTA:
Oliver?

34:39.997 --> 34:42.583
[water running]

34:42.583 --> 34:44.835
I'm waiting...

34:46.587 --> 34:49.590
♪ gentle piano melody playing ♪

34:49.590 --> 34:51.592
♪
